facility. LNG is shipped in leased LNG carriers destined for sale globally.
QG3 executed the development of the onshore and offshore assets as a single integrated development with Qatargas 4 (QG4), a
joint venture between Qatar Petroleum and Royal Dutch Shell plc. This included the joint development of offshore facilities
situated in a common offshore block in the North Field, as well as the construction of two identical LNG process trains and
associated gas treating facilities for both the QG3 and QG4 joint ventures. Production from the LNG trains and associated facilities
is combined and shared.
