2017 vs. 2016
Net interest consists of interest and financing expense, net of interest income and capitalized interest. Net interest decreased
25 percent in 2017 compared with 2016, primarily due to impacts from the fair market value method of apportioning interest
expense in the United States and lower interest as a result of reduced debt. Higher interest income further drove the decrease in net
