We have deferred tax assets related to certain accrued liabilities, loss carryforwards and credit carryforwards. Valuation allowances
have been established to reduce these deferred tax assets to an amount that will, more likely than not, be realized. Based on our
historical taxable income, our expectations for the future, and available tax-planning strategies, management expects the net
deferred tax assets will be realized as offsets to reversing deferred tax liabilities.
 
