Financial Instruments
We invest excess cash in financial instruments with maturities based on our cash forecasts for the various currency pools we
manage. The maturities of these investments may from time to time extend beyond 90 days. The types of financial instruments that
we currently invest include:
 
 • Time deposits: Interest bearing deposits placed with approved financial institutions.
 • Commercial paper: Unsecured promissory notes issued by a corporation, commercial bank or government agency
purchased at a discount to mature at par.
 • Government or government agency obligations: Short-term securities issued by the U.S. government or U.S. government
agencies.
 
