to U.S. tax basis and foreign tax credits associated with our foreign branch assets that we do not expect to realize. Based on our
historical taxable income, expectations for the future, and available tax-planning strategies, management expects deferred tax
assets, net of valuation allowance, will primarily be realized as offsets to reversing deferred tax liabilities.
 
